<http://www.spektrix.com/ccoa/event/250001AJDCLDMKGKGLQVDQDPLQDBLBRGV> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Anne of Green Gables - Sensory Friendly Performance";
  schema:description """
	<h2>A SENSORY-FRIENDLY PERFORMANCE</h2><span><br/></span>As part of our ongoing commitment to accessibility, the Centre is offering a <span class=\"BoldText\">Sensory Friendly Performance</span>. This is a <span class=\"BoldText\">full, live performance</span> featuring the complete cast and production, with thoughtful adjustments to help make the theatre environment more comfortable for those who may be sensory-sensitive, experience anxiety, or prefer a less intense theatre setting.<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>What is Sensory-Friendly?<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Sensory-friendly performances are designed to support a wide range of audience members, including those who are neurodivergent, pregnant individuals, nursing parents, seniors, people with service animals, and anyone who may benefit from reduced sensory stimulation.<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>What can I expect?<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The performance itself remains unchanged; however, select environmental elements will be adjusted to reduce sensory impact. These modifications are intended to create a welcoming and inclusive experience without altering the artistic integrity of the show.<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>What is different?<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Sensory-friendly adjustments:</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>•	Same Show – The performance itself is the same<span><br/></span>•	Lights Up a Little – House lights remaining on at a low level throughout the performance<span><br/></span>•	Lower Sound Levels – Reduced overall sound levels<span><br/></span>•	Advance Warnings – Advance warnings or adjustments for sudden loud noises or rapid lighting effects<span><br/></span>•	Flexibility – Flexible seating, allowing patrons to enter or exit the theatre as needed<span><br/></span>•	Devise Use – Use of electronic devices permitted with sound turned off<span><br/></span>•	Easy Movement – Audience members are welcome to move, stretch, or step out during the performance as needed.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-09-01T13:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/ccoa/location/201AGBHDRLQHNHPHKKMPKLGPMDRDTDMVL>;
  schema:offers _:8bf1a82a9b7c466fab0eeb10a30b98201483;
  schema:duration "PT155M";
  schema:endDate "2026-09-01T15:35:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

